node.text: Since this video was recorded, recent rains over much of Eastern Australia have provided some relief for firefighters. Having said that, the summer and the fire season is far from over and in a warming climate, we will experience longer more intense bushfire events. Please watch til the end for some ways you can help moving forward ❤️ @attndotcom

node.text:
Day 8 (I think) of hotel quarantine in Sydney. Jonesing for fresh air but mostly feeling relieved I got home before the lock down and just feeling heartbroken for all the Aussies that are struggling to get home to their families (thanks Scomo you actual human garbage). 
If you’re in Australia and confused about the vaccine messaging, that’s fair! ...But please please please, go get ya jab when it’s available so we can all be done with this rubbish!

Started a @poshmark closet and listing this bad boy! Get notified when this summer tote is available by downloading the app, following my closet ‘themaiamitchell’ & “hearting” the listing. 
One garbage trucks' worth of textiles is landfilled or burned every second, making fashion one of the top-polluting industries. Poshmark makes buying and selling simple and sustainable. Extend the life cycle of items in your closet you no longer wear and contribute to a more circular, sustainable future for fashion by listing on Poshmark today.
Comment with your poshmark closet name below so I can follow you 🤗
